‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Newmarch was born about 1385. He had at least 1 daughter with Joan Shirley. He died before 1428, and was buried in Wormsley, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1385–Bef 1428":"umbes 1385–enne 1428","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","1390–1452":"1390–1452","1418–1467":"1418–1467","1385–1428":"1385–1428","about 1418":"umbes 1418","1467":"1467","Abt 1385":"umbes 1385","1452":"1452","1385":"1385","Bef 1428":"enne 1428","1418":"1418","1428":"1428","1390":"1390","Womersley, Yorkshire, England":"Womersley, Yorkshire, England","Wormsley, Herefordshire Unitary Authority, Herefordshire, England":"Wormsley, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1385–Bef 1428":"noin 1385–ennen vuotta 1428","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","1390–1452":"1390–1452","1418–1467":"1418–1467","1385–1428":"1385–1428","about 1418":"noin 1418","1467":"1467","Abt 1385":"noin 1385","1452":"1452","1385":"1385","Bef 1428":"ennen vuotta 1428","1418":"1418","1428":"1428","1390":"1390","Womersley, Yorkshire, England":"Womersley, Yorkshire, England","Wormsley, Herefordshire Unitary Authority, Herefordshire, England":"Wormsley, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1385–Bef 1428":"environ 1385–avant 1428","1390–Female":"1390–Décédée","1390–1452":"1390–1452","1418–1467":"1418–1467","1385–1428"